From: pocknix
Subject: [PATCH] Revert "mangoapp: Always send output frametimings even when not FIFO"

Reverts upstream e572411d. Two measured reasons (docs/gamescope-fps-investigation.md
"GPU-side session", 2026-07-02):

1. THE STRADDLE: e572411d moved mangoapp's redraw trigger from commit_t::Signal (fires at
   game COMMIT time, before the frame is composited) to mangoapp_output_update (fires in
   the output handler, AFTER the composite). Post-composite, mangoapp's redraw always
   arrives too late to be coalesced into its own frame's composite, so gamescope runs an
   extra full rotated composite (~2.5-3.9ms of GPU on the RP6) for the overlay alone —
   measured at ~16 extra composites/s on a ~48fps game even with the mangoapp pacing fix
   (mangohud patch 0006) in place. Pre-composite nudge = the redraw usually rides along in
   the same composite = overlay ~free. This matches ROCKNIX's gamescope (4286887, which
   predates e572411d) — the reference setup where the overlay costs nothing.

2. THE READOUT: post-e572411d the frametimes mangoapp receives are output-handler
   vblank-timestamp deltas, quantized to 8.33ms multiples at 120Hz — the overlay displayed
   "45 fps" while hardware counters retired 55. The commit-path frametimes this restores
   are the game's real present cadence.

--- a/src/commit.cpp
+++ b/src/commit.cpp
@@ -91,7 +91,7 @@
     }

     if ( m_bMangoNudge )
-        mangoapp_update( uint64_t(~0ull), frametime, uint64_t(~0ull) );
+        mangoapp_update( IsPerfOverlayFIFO() ? uint64_t(~0ull) : frametime, frametime, uint64_t(~0ull) );
 }

 void commit_t::OnPollHangUp()
--- a/src/mangoapp.cpp
+++ b/src/mangoapp.cpp
@@ -77,6 +77,11 @@

 void mangoapp_output_update( uint64_t vblanktime )
 {
+    if ( !g_bCurrentBasePlaneIsFifo )
+    {
+        return;
+    }
+
 	static uint64_t s_uLastBasePlaneCommitID = 0;
 	if ( s_uLastBasePlaneCommitID != g_uCurrentBasePlaneCommitID )
 	{
